    <div class="row">
        <div class="taboo taboo-img col-lg-5 col-md col-sm">
            <img src="images/taboo-bordered.png" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="text-field taboo taboo-text col-lg-7 col-md col-sm">
            <h1>Religious Taboos</h1>
            <p>In India , a majority of people hesitate to donate their organs , believing it would interfere with their
                religious practices. However, every religion has the principle saying of humanity and brotherhood. If
                you can be of help to someone even after dying , why not do so?</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="text-field ed-lack ed-lack-text col-lg-7 col-md col-sm">
            <h1>Lack of Education</h1>
            <p>Lack of educational programs on organ donation and transplantation has been pointed out before as one of
                the main reasons for organ shortage. Therefore , we aim to educate and encourage the students</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ed-lack ed-lack-img col-lg-5 col-md col-sm">
            <img src="images/girl-crying-bordered.png" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="myth myth-img col-lg-5 col-md col-sm">
            <img src="images/myths-vs-facts-bordered.png" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="text-field myth myth-text col-lg-7 col-md col-sm">
            <h1>Myths</h1>
            <p>There are many myths that can be misguiding people like:
                <br>
                1. Only family members can donate organs.
                <br>
                2. You can't have an open casket if you've been an organ donor.
                <br>
                All of these are false, in fact organ donation is encouraged by all religions and anyone can help the
                needy.
            </p>
        </div>
